{"abstract":[{"text":"This parameter defines the range for the fade-out effect before an automatic content cutoff on pitched map views. Fade out is implemented by scaling down and removing buildings in the fade range in a staggered fashion. Opacity is not changed. The fade range is expressed in relation to the height of the map view. A value of 1.0 indicates that the content is faded to the same extent as the map’s height in pixels, while a value close to zero represents a sharp cutoff. When the value is set to 0.0, the cutoff is completely disabled. Note: The property has no effect on the map if terrain is enabled.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Default value: 0. Value range: [0, 1]"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.mapbox.MapboxMaps\/documentation\/Overview","doc:\/\/com.mapbox.MapboxMaps\/documentation\/MapboxMaps","doc:\/\/com.mapbox.MapboxMaps\/documentation\/MapboxMaps\/Layers","doc:\/\/com.mapbox.MapboxMaps\/documentation\/MapboxMaps\/FillExtrusionLayer"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"fillExtrusionCutoffFadeRange","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Value","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.mapbox.MapboxMaps\/documentation\/MapboxMaps\/Value","preciseIdentifier":"s:10MapboxMaps5ValueO","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd","text":"Double","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":">?"}]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/mapboxmaps\/fillextrusionlayer\/fillextrusioncutofffaderange"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/com.mapbox.MapboxMaps\/documentation\/MapboxMaps\/FillExtrusionLayer\/fillExtrusionCutoffFadeRange"},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"externalID":"s:10MapboxMaps18FillExtrusionLayerV04fillD15CutoffFadeRangeAA5ValueOySdGSgvp","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"fillExtrusionCutoffFadeRange","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:10MapboxMaps5ValueO","text":"Value","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"Double","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd"},{"text":">?","kind":"text"}],"title":"fillExtrusionCutoffFadeRange","modules":[{"name":"MapboxMaps"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"property","roleHeading":"Instance Property"},"references":{"doc://com.mapbox.MapboxMaps/documentation/MapboxMaps/FillExtrusionLayer/fillExtrusionCutoffFadeRange":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"fillExtrusionCutoffFadeRange","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Value","preciseIdentifier":"s:10MapboxMaps5ValueO","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd","text":"Double"},{"kind":"text","text":">?"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.mapbox.MapboxMaps\/documentation\/MapboxMaps\/FillExtrusionLayer\/fillExtrusionCutoffFadeRange","type":"topic","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/mapboxmaps\/fillextrusionlayer\/fillextrusioncutofffaderange","abstract":[{"text":"This parameter defines the range for the fade-out effect before an automatic content cutoff on pitched map views. Fade out is implemented by scaling down and removing buildings in the fade range in a staggered fashion. Opacity is not changed. The fade range is expressed in relation to the height of the map view. A value of 1.0 indicates that the content is faded to the same extent as the map’s height in pixels, while a value close to zero represents a sharp cutoff. When the value is set to 0.0, the cutoff is completely disabled. Note: The property has no effect on the map if terrain is enabled.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Def